text:
The COVID-19 pandemic was confirmed to have reached Equatorial Guinea on 14 March 2020.
Equatorial Guinea has a weak healthcare system.
The country's first case was announced on 14 March, a 42-year-old woman in Malabo, who returned to Equatorial Guinea from Madrid.
As of March 24, there were 9 cases in the country, all imported. There were no confirmed cases of community spread in the country at the time.
